race.comment: EQUAL POWER (6) is ready to win after she just missed last time, beaten a head into second over 1000m at Mitchell after being prominent from the outset. Has the speed to be prominent and is hard to beat in this suitable race. GLUTTONY (4) resumed from a spell last start with a sound third over 1000m at Clifton. Suitably placed to crack the maiden win. DESTINY GUNGHO (1) was in the money two starts back at Tara then missed the frame but was not too far away last time over 1000m at Mitchell. Best form stacks up and he is among the chances. LADY ENCRYPTEAU (9) raced on the speed from the outset last start and finished second, beaten 2.25 lengths, over 950m at Moree. This is an easier assignment and can get the job done.
